          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-8126727a1c891978",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Dormant (Inactive) Accounts\nA CIBC account is considered dormant if you haven\u2019t initiated any transactions for a 24-month period. Dormant accounts that receive a monthly statement will automatically be switched to quarterly statements.\nNote: After 10 years, if your account remains dormant, your Canadian dollar balance is transferred to the Bank of Canada.\nTo activate a dormant account, you can:\nMake a deposit, withdrawal, transfer or bill payment at any CIBC branch or CIBC bank machine; or\nDeposit a cheque with your mobile device using CIBC eDeposit \u2122 ; or\nMake a withdrawal at any other bank machine displaying the Interac , Visa or Plus logo; or\nMake a debit purchase\nCall CIBC Telephone Banking at 1- 800- 465-2422 Opens your phone app.\nStatus\nFee/Year\nDormant for 2, 3 or 4 years\n$20.00 6\nDormant for 5, 6, 7 or 8 years\n$30.00 6\nDormant for 9 years\n$40.00 6",
