          "source_snapshot_id": "snap-66da89330de2237a",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-e5ecb511dd12beca",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Your questions answered\nWhen you open a Canadian bank account, you'll receive a debit card and a personal identification number (PIN) for security. You can use these to pay for products and services. When you pay with a debit card, the money is immediately withdrawn from your account to pay the merchant.\nThis is a fast, safe way to transfer money to another person within Canada. All you need is the recipient's email address or Canadian mobile phone number. We'll take care of the rest. Learn more about how to send an Interac e-Transfer .\nYou can easily send money internationally from your CIBC bank account in one of 2 ways.\nRequesting a Global Money Transfer:\nAfter you sign on to online banking, choose Global Money Transfer. To learn more about how to send money globally, visit Global Money Transfer .\nRequesting a wire transfer:\nVisit us in person at a CIBC Banking Centre Opens a new",
