          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-1c8bca2b2a6ee3cb",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Can I hold a GIC in a TFSA or RRSP?\nYes, you can hold a GIC in a TFSA (Tax-Free Savings Account) or RRSP (Registered Retirement Savings Plan). In a TFSA, the interest earned grows tax-free, with tax-free withdrawals. In an RRSP, the interest grows tax-deferred and is taxed upon withdrawal. GICs are a secure investment that have the potential to earn investment returns, and holding them in registered accounts adds tax benefits, making them a suitable choice for long-term financial planning.",
