        {
          "field_name": "tax_benefits",
          "candidate_value": "If you hold your GICs in a registered account such as a TFSA or RRSP you could grow your money tax-free or tax-deferred, respectively.",
          "evidence_chunk_id": "chunk-4309d5253cfdb743",
          "evidence_text_excerpt": "Are there any tax implications for GIC interest income?\nIt depends on what type of account the GICs are held in such as registered or non-registered.\nIf you hold your GICs in a registered account such as a TFSA or RRSP you could grow your money tax-free or tax-deferred, respectively. However, if you hold your GIC in a non-registered account, the interest rate that you earn each year is generally taxed as income. TD Bank does not provide tax advice, and you should consult your tax advisor regarding your individual tax situation.\nLegal",
