          "evidence_text_excerpt": "e\nSchedule on page 7 for a list of the services you may choose to use with\nyour account and the applicable service fee.\nTransaction fee\nFor some of our accounts, you pay a transaction fee for each transaction\nthat takes money out of your account. For these accounts, you can\ncomplete a set number of transactions per month where we will not\ncharge you a transaction fee. If you exceed the set number of transactions\nper month, you may pay a transaction fee based on your account type.\nTransaction fees are calculated based on the account type you hold on the\nlast day of the month. Some transaction types may not count toward the\ntransaction fee limit. For example, purchases made with your TD Access\nCard at most Canadian public transit agencies/merchants will not count\ntoward the monthly transaction limit of your account. Some examples of\ntransactions include withdrawals, cheques, bill",
